The paper proposes a neuro-evolution algorithm for optimizing recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the algorithm is based on ant colony optimization, which is a nature-inspired optimization technique. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of regularization techniques and the incorporation of specialized ant agents, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve time series data, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the data involves visual information.
